            <h3>HOW TO SAVE YOUNGSTERS FROM DRUGS ?</h3><br>
            <p>There are many ways to protect young people from drugs. Here are some strategies that can help:</p><br>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Talk to them openly: Educate young people about the risks of drug use and the impact it can have on their lives. Be open, honest, and non-judgmental when discussing drug use and provide accurate information.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Be a positive role model: Model healthy behaviors, including avoiding drug use and managing stress in healthy ways.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Provide alternatives: Offer young people opportunities to engage in healthy activities, such as sports, music, or other hobbies, that can provide a sense of fulfillment and purpose.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Monitor their activities: Keep an eye on young people's activities and monitor their social media and internet use.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Seek help if needed: If you suspect that a young person is struggling with drug use or addiction, seek help from a qualified professional or addiction specialist.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
