            <h3>RECOVERY FROM DRUG ADDICTIVE</h3>
            <p>Recovering from drug addiction can be a challenging and complex process, but it is possible with the right treatment and support. 
            Here are some method one can try to overcome from drug addiction:</p><br>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <b>Acknowledge the problem:</b> The first step to recovery is recognizing that there is a problem and acknowledging the impact that drug addiction has had on your life and the lives of those around you.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <b>Seek professional help:</b> Treatment for drug addiction may involve detoxification, medication, and behavioral therapy. Seek help from a qualified addiction specialist or medical professional who can develop a personalized treatment plan tailored to your needs.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <b>Avoid triggers:</b> Identify and avoid situations or people that may trigger drug use. This may involve changing your environment, avoiding certain social situations, or learning coping strategies to deal with triggers.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <b>Develop healthy habits:</b> Engage in activities that promote physical and mental well-being, such as exercise, meditation, and therapy. Create a routine that promotes healthy eating, good sleep hygiene, and self-care.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <b>Build a support system:</b> Recovery is easier with support from family, friends, or a support group. Connect with others who are going through similar experiences and build a strong support system to help you through the recovery process.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
